<plot>Two music students, well-versed in physics, launch their adventure in post-modern England, moving on through ancient Ireland, Wales, Scotland, and north Britain, as it was becoming England. The trick to surviving both the physical challenge of meeting barbaric tribes and the supernatural challenge of overcoming mysterious - even wrathful - gods and other creatures of myth, is the peaceful use of physics. The two students have mastered the physics (and metaphysics) of guitar and vocal sound-waves, while their drummer-companion has mastered the mechanics of magnetic and temporal locomotion (a magnetic time tower). So relax and enjoy the 13 short, hard-rock songs and hundreds of digital paintings of mythic times, as the story-elements are so densely-packed, you'll need a dozen views to catch most of them!</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?059367</url></doc>
